{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Stage-2 bounded LLM pairwise overlap judge (advisory findings + suggested link commands)\n\n## Why\nPrecision lives in stage 2, not in a similarity threshold. The recall spike (epic experiment comment) showed retrieval recall is excellent BUT flagged precision-at-scale as the residual risk (same model produces query+doc digests ‚Üí vocabularies converge ‚Üí near-duplicates converge too). This judge IS that precision mitigation: a bounded LLM pairwise classifier over the ~K stage-1 candidates.\n\n## What ‚ÄĒ output schema (fully specified, DIRECTED)\nOutput `overlap_verdict` (register in `contracts.py`): `{relation: enum, shared_artifact: string|null, confidence: number, abstain: bool}`, `relation ‚ąą {duplicates, supersedes, depends_on, related_distinct, unrelated}` (CLOSED). The judge is prompted with an ORDERED pair (First, Second) and its `relation` is read DIRECTIONALLY as \"First `relation` Second\" (e.g. `supersedes` ‚áí \"First supersedes Second\"; `depends_on` ‚áí \"First depends_on Second\"). Only `duplicates|supersedes|depends_on` are surfaceable; the `rebar link` relation set is the 6 built-ins (`blocks, depends_on, relates_to, duplicates, supersedes, discovered_from`) ‚ÄĒ the judge only ever emits the three surfaceable ones.\n- Both orderings run: ordering-1 = (Q=query, C=candidate) ‚Üí r1 = \"Q r1 C\"; ordering-2 = (C, Q) ‚Üí r2 = \"C r2 Q\". AGGREGATION (fail-safe toward \"distinct\"; each side must cite a non-null `shared_artifact` and both `confidence >= overlap_conf_threshold`, else downgrade to `related_distinct`, not surfaced; an `abstain:true` in EITHER ordering also downgrades and consumes no surface slot):\n  - **`duplicates` (symmetric):** surface iff r1 == r2 == `duplicates`.\n  - **`supersedes`/`depends_on` (DIRECTIONAL):** surface iff exactly ONE ordering asserts the directional relation and the other is DIRECTION-CONSISTENT (not the same label pointing the other way). Concretely, r1 ‚ąą {supersedes,depends_on} is surfaced as \"Q r1 C\" only if r2 does NOT assert the reciprocal \"C r1 Q\" (r2 ‚ąą {related_distinct, unrelated, or the inverse}). If BOTH orderings assert the same directional label with opposite subjects (r1=\"Q supersedes C\" AND r2=\"C supersedes Q\"), that is a self-contradiction ‚Üí downgrade to `related_distinct` (not surfaced). This resolves the inverted-`link_command` ambiguity: the surfaced direction is taken from the single ordering that consistently asserts it.\n- Surface ‚Č§ `overlap_surface_cap` (default 3) highest-confidence results: `{source_id, target_id, relation, shared_artifact, confidence, link_command}`. The `link_command` uses the DIRECTED pair: for a directional relation, `rebar link <source_id> <target_id> <relation>` where (source‚Üítarget) is the asserting ordering's (First‚ÜíSecond) ‚ÄĒ so \"Q supersedes C\" ‚áí `rebar link Q C supersedes` and \"C supersedes Q\" ‚áí `rebar link C Q supersedes` (never both). For symmetric `duplicates`, canonicalize the pair by sorted ticket-id so the command is deterministic: `rebar link <min(Q,C)> <max(Q,C)> duplicates`.\n- K candidates ‚Üí 2K judge calls (both orderings), flat in corpus size.\n- Errors: LLM timeout/error/malformed output on a candidate ‚Üí treated as `abstain` (dropped), logged; never raises to the caller.\n\n## Config (LLMConfig, not VerifyConfig) ‚ÄĒ with explicit `from_env` wiring\n`overlap_conf_threshold: float = 0.7`, `overlap_surface_cap: int = 3` on `LLMConfig`\n(`src/rebar/llm/config.py`, `[tool.rebar.llm]`, `REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_*`) ‚ÄĒ LLM tunables;\n`_config_schema.py` reserves `llm.*`, so NOT `VerifyConfig`. **`from_env()` MUST be edited**\n(it constructs `LLMConfig(...)` reading every field via a helper): add module constants\n`DEFAULT_OVERLAP_CONF_THRESHOLD = 0.7` / `DEFAULT_OVERLAP_SURFACE_CAP = 3`, the two dataclass\nfields, and in `from_env`'s `return cls(...)`:\n- `overlap_conf_threshold=_llm_float(table, cli, \"REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_CONF_THRESHOLD\", \"overlap_conf_threshold\", DEFAULT_OVERLAP_CONF_THRESHOLD)`\n- `overlap_surface_cap=_llm_int(table, cli, \"REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_SURFACE_CAP\", \"overlap_surface_cap\", DEFAULT_OVERLAP_SURFACE_CAP)`\n\n(`_llm_float` is added by S2 wood-heedless-sheldrake, a sibling ‚ÄĒ if S2 has not landed in the\nstack yet, this story adds it, mirroring `_llm_int`.)\n\n## Dependencies\nS5 (`OverlapCandidate` interface + query/corpus digests). Consumed by S7. (S5 is a sibling story; a codebase grep won't find `OverlapCandidate` until it lands.)\n\n## Scope\n- New `src/rebar/llm/overlap/judge.py` + rubric prompt `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/overlap_judge.md` (`execution_mode: single_turn`, `outputs: overlap_verdict`, `category: overlap`) whose body MUST encode: the CLOSED 5-value `relation` classification ({duplicates, supersedes, depends_on, related_distinct, unrelated} ‚ÄĒ only the first three surfaceable), the require-a-cited-shared-artifact gate, the both-orderings instruction, and the abstain-when-unsure criterion.\n- `overlap_verdict` schema `src/rebar/schemas/overlap_verdict.schema.json` + `register_contract(\"overlap_verdict\", <builder>)` at the bottom of `contracts.py` (co-located with `response_model_for`, guaranteeing registration before use). WIRE the schema in `src/rebar/schemas/__init__.py` (`OVERLAP_VERDICT = \"overlap_verdict\"`, `OUTPUT_SCHEMAS[\"overlap_judge\"] = OVERLAP_VERDICT`, add to `__all__`) so `test_every_schema_file_is_wired` passes.\n- **Deliverable ‚ÄĒ labeled fixtures:** `tests/fixtures/overlap_pairs/` with ‚Č•12 labeled pairs (each `{a_digest, b_digest, gold_relation}`), COMMITTED as part of this story (consumed by `test_judge_precision_recall`).\n- Config field wiring in `src/rebar/llm/config.py` (enumerated above).\n- OUT: retrieval (S5), wiring (S7).\n\n## Testing\n- `tests/unit/test_overlap_judge.py` (FakeRunner): `test_agree` (both agree+artifact ‚Üí surfaced); `test_disagree_downgrade`; `test_requires_artifact` (null artifact ‚Üí not surfaced); `test_abstain_dropped` (no slot consumed); `test_cap` (‚Č§ surface_cap); `test_link_command` (valid relation string); `test_directional_link_command` (for `supersedes`/`depends_on`, the emitted `link_command` uses the asserting ordering's source‚Üítarget direction ‚ÄĒ `rebar link Q C supersedes` NOT `C Q`; and a both-orderings-same-directional-label contradiction downgrades to `related_distinct`); `test_duplicates_canonical` (`duplicates` command uses sorted-id pair, deterministic); `test_llm_error_abstain` (no raise); `test_config` (sets `REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_CONF_THRESHOLD` and `REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_SURFACE_CAP`, asserts `LLMConfig.from_env()` resolves both from the env ‚ÄĒ proving `from_env` wiring, not just defaults).\n- Precision/recall check as a PYTEST FIXTURE test (NOT the prompt-eval harness ‚ÄĒ no registered scorer exists for the `overlap_verdict` shape): `test_judge_precision_recall` (a deterministic UNIT test: a FakeRunner returns canned per-pair `overlap_verdict`s over a LABELED fixture of ‚Č•12 pairs at `tests/fixtures/overlap_pairs/`, no live LLM) computes precision AND recall and asserts precision ‚Č•0.8 AND recall ‚Č•0.6 (the recall floor stops an abstain-everything judge from trivially passing). Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_overlap_judge.py::test_judge_precision_recall`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Judges both orderings, aggregates by the stated rule; `pytest ...::{test_agree,test_disagree_downgrade}`.\n- [ ] Surfaces only with a non-null `shared_artifact`, else `related_distinct`; `::test_requires_artifact`. Abstain drops without consuming a slot; `::test_abstain_dropped`.\n- [ ] ‚Č§ `overlap_surface_cap` (default 3) findings, each `{source_id, target_id, relation‚ąą{duplicates,supersedes,depends_on}, shared_artifact, confidence, link_command}`; the `link_command` is DIRECTED correctly (directional relation uses the asserting ordering's source‚Üítarget; `duplicates` uses sorted-id canonical pair); `::{test_cap,test_link_command,test_directional_link_command,test_duplicates_canonical}`.\n- [ ] LLM error on a candidate ‚Üí abstain, logged, no raise; `::test_llm_error_abstain`.\n- [ ] Fixture test `test_judge_precision_recall` (‚Č•12 labeled pairs) asserts precision ‚Č•0.8 AND recall ‚Č•0.6; `::test_judge_precision_recall`.\n- [ ] `overlap_conf_threshold` (0.7) and `overlap_surface_cap` (3) are read from the env by `LLMConfig.from_env()` (explicit wiring, `_llm_float` for the threshold); `::test_config`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783648615995352001,"uuid":"644639fe-56e1-4715-a1af-39c84c661621"}